    {
        "content": "<p>mathlib <del>'s naming</del> is inconsistent: it's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.convexHull_image#doc\">docs#LinearMap.convexHull_image</a>, but <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AffineMap.image_convexHull#doc\">docs#AffineMap.image_convexHull</a>. Is there any reason why these should be different? Which direction should be preferred?</p>",
        "id": 425937239,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1710171530
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've filed <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/11298\">#11298</a>, adapting the <code>AffineMap</code> lemma to the <code>LinearMap</code> version, but I'll be happy to change things the other way.</p>",
        "id": 425937828,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1710171664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It’s not a naming issue. Both names are correct. The issue that those lemmas have different opinions about sides.</p>",
        "id": 425937870,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1710171678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I know!</p>",
        "id": 425937923,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1710171691
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The question is, is there a good reason the lemmas have different sides? Or should one flip one of them to match the other?</p>",
        "id": 425938010,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1710171713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And clearly this has to be fixed.</p>",
        "id": 425938040,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1710171722
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I’m sure this is an accident.</p>",
        "id": 425938163,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1710171741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can wait a bit to see whether someone has strong opinion but I guess picking one at random is fine.</p>",
        "id": 425938321,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1710171777
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I have a strong opinion and in fact meant to fix it and forgot several months ago.</p>",
        "id": 426003088,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1710188885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It should be <code>f '' convexHull _ _ = convexHull _ (f '' s)</code>, the same way we have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=map_add#doc\">docs#map_add</a></p>",
        "id": 426003235,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1710188934
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you for the input. I have now flipped both lemmas to match this convention.<br>\nThe diff includes two lemmas, for which I'm wondering if they should be flipped as well.</p>",
